  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:219:### Providing the tests that use docker
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:221:If your tests use Docker (either with explicit Docker process invocation or through some library method call), all images have to be declared in `required-docker-images` file.
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:224:Only Docker images that are listed in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images) can be used for testing.
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:226:That pull request should add a new file in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images)
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:227:with the name in the format `Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>` (replace all occurrence of `/` with `_`) .
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:228:The only line that this file needs to contain is `FROM <dockerImageName>`.
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:232:grype <dockerImageName>
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:236:   * If your test uses Docker image, and you didn't specify it in the `required-docker-images.txt` file, the test will fail.
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:237:   * If your test uses Docker image that is not listed in [allowed docker images list](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/AllowedDockerImages.txt),
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:239:   * Only docker images that are in both `required-docker-images.txt` and in the `allowed docker images list`
  ./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:243:See an [example](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-mysql_mysql-server).
