t](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/AllowedDockerImages.txt),\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:239:   * Only docker images that are in both `required-docker-images.txt` and in the `allowed docker images list`\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:243:See an [example](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-mysql_mysql-server).\n./docs/tests.md:16:  Docker images it needs in `required-docker-images.txt`, and is the unit the\n./docs/tests.md:59:  declared, pre-pulled `allowed-docker-image` with networking disabled, and\n./COVERAGE.md:112:| `com.github.docker-java:docker-java-api` | [3.2.13<br>- 3.7.1](metadata/com.github.docker-java/docker-java-api/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> docker-java-api provides the command interfaces, model types, and callback contracts for Java clients that talk to the Docker Remote API. It is the API layer used by docker-java implementations to define container, image, network, volume, swarm, and system operations without binding callers to a specific transport.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/com.github.docker-java/docker-java-api/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:113:| `com.github.docker-java:docker-java-transport` | [3.2.13<br>- 3.7.1](metadata/com.github.docker-java/docker-java-transport/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> docker-java-transport provides the core transport abstractions and shared utilities used by docker-java clients to communicate with the Docker Remote API. It defines common request and response plumbing that concrete transport implementations build on.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/com.github.docker-java/docker-java-transport/) |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:125:| `docker` | PR | PR updates allowed Docker images used by tests. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Declared Docker images.** Tests that use Docker must declare every image they need in `required-docker-images.txt`. Each image must already appear in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>`. Tests fail otherwise.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:240:- **Docker isolation.** Docker images used in tests are pre-pulled from `allowed-docker-images`, after which the runner disables Docker networking for deterministic, isolated test runs.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:244:- **Docker tag sync.** Dependabot updates to `allowed-docker-images` trigger `sync-docker-tags.yml`, which back-commits the synchronized tags into the Dependabot PR.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:259:- **Determinism.** Tests must be reproducible. Network-dependent tests are not allowed except where they declare an `allowed-docker-image` and run against that pre-pulled image with networking disabled.\n./docs/tck.md:103:| `checkAllowedDockerImages` | Scan allowed images for vulnerabilities with grype, either all images or only those changed between two commits (§CI-scan-docker-images). |\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:49:DOCKER_IMAGE_LIST_COMMAND = [\"docker\", \"image\", \"ls\", \"--format\", \"{{.Repository}}:{{.Tag}} {{.ID}}\"]\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:282:    if _should_run_docker_scan(changed_files):\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:285:            \"docker-image-scan\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:750:def _should_run_docker_scan(changed_files: list[str]) -> bool:\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:751:    return any(path.startswith(\"tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/\") for path in changed_files)\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:768:        if not _coordinate_uses_docker(repo_path, coordinates):\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:773:            \"pull-allowed-docker-images\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:798:        failed = _run_recorded_command_without_new