e-<dockerImageName>`. Tests fail otherwise.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:240:- **Docker isolation.** Docker images used in tests are pre-pulled from `allowed-docker-images`, after which the runner disables Docker networking for deterministic, isolated test runs.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:244:- **Docker tag sync.** Dependabot updates to `allowed-docker-images` trigger `sync-docker-tags.yml`, which back-commits the synchronized tags into the Dependabot PR.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:259:- **Determinism.** Tests must be reproducible. Network-dependent tests are not allowed except where they declare an `allowed-docker-image` and run against that pre-pulled image with networking disabled.\n./docs/tck.md:103:| `checkAllowedDockerImages` | Scan allowed images for vulnerabilities with grype, either all images or only those changed between two commits (§CI-scan-docker-images). |\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:49:DOCKER_IMAGE_LIST_COMMAND = [\"docker\", \"image\", \"ls\", \"--format\", \"{{.Repository}}:{{.Tag}} {{.ID}}\"]\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:282:    if _should_run_docker_scan(changed_files):\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:285:            \"docker-image-scan\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:750:def _should_run_docker_scan(changed_files: list[str]) -> bool:\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:751:    return any(path.startswith(\"tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/\") for path in changed_files)\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:768:        if not _coordinate_uses_docker(repo_path, coordinates):\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:773:            \"pull-allowed-docker-images\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:798:        failed = _run_recorded_command_without_new_docker_images(\n./forge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:886:def _coordinate_uses_docker(repo_path: str, coordinates: str) -> bool:\n./f